  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To determine if proprietary software that uses pulse-wave analysis to interpret the output of
      a conventional pulse-oximeter, can predict the onset of circulatory stress, before changes in
      blood pressure and pulse occur, in patients undergoing outpatient hemodialysis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
